data.title: Come Around (Sing It Loud album)
data.text:
2008 studio album by Sing It Loud

Professional ratingsReview scoresSourceRatingAllMusic[1]AbsolutePunk(57/100)[2]Rock Sound[3]

Come Around is the debut studio album from Minneapolis, Minnesota pop rock band Sing It Loud. It was released on Epitaph Records on September 23, 2008. The band toured with Valencia in August and September 2008, prior to their own headlining tour, and then a supporting slot for Cobra Starship until November 2008.[4] On April 21, 2009, a music video was released for "Don't Save Me".[5] Between June and August 2009, the band appeared on the Warped Tour.[6]

Notes

[edit]

The band's previous drummer, Dane Schmidt, plays drums and sings backup vocals on this album. He was replaced by Chris "Sick Boy" Lee several months after the album was recorded.
